							<p>If you use the Internet to exchange information with Alistithmar Capital, you will be able to see when you are secured during information exchange, when a “locked” icon is displayed at the bottom of the screen or when https:// appears in the address line. This is often referred to as a ‘secured session’. You can increase your level of security by memorizing your password and by changing it regularly. You should try to avoid using passwords that can be guessed by people who know you or who have information about you – for example, avoid passwords that contain your birth date, your name or parts of your name, or that include any well-known values such as your phone number, your car registration, your customer or account number. If you must write down your password, please make sure you keep this written record securely stored.</p>
